-- Ivory Coast Leads North Korea 2-0 at Cup Game After Toure, Romaric Goals
-- Chris Elser
-- 2010-06-25T14:26:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/ivory-coast-leads-north-korea-2-0-at-cup-game-after-toure-romaric-goals.html

          
          
             The Ivory Coast leads North Korea 2-
0 after goals from Romaric and Yaya Toure in their final World
Cup Group G match in Nelspruit, South Africa.  
 Toure scored in the 14th minute and 6 minutes later the
team got another one when Romaric headed in a rebound from
Didier Drogba, who had hit the cross bar.  
 In the other match in the group, Brazil meets Portugal in
Durban. Brazil leads the group with six points after two
victories. Portugal is second with 4 points, with the Ivory
Coast on 1 and the North Koreans with none.  
 In todayâ€™s late matches in Group H, Chile takes on Spain in
Pretoria, and Switzerland meets Honduras in Bloemfontein.  
          
          


  


        